      <section id="id1171807690657">
        <title>Stripes and Stars – Part 1</title>
        <para id="id1171808538328">Long, long ago</para>
        <para id="id1171802142693">and far, far away –</para>
        <para id="id1171802033720">when there were no cities or towns.</para>
        <para id="id1171809261956">no trains or cars or aeroplanes.</para>
        <para id="id1171810225909">no people living on the earth –</para>
        <para id="id1171802221953">there were great, green forests</para>
        <para id="id1171802943831">that covered the earth,</para>
        <para id="id1171806844106">from the seashores</para>
        <para id="id1171809651789">up to the highest mountains.</para>
        <para id="id1171810725308">There were wide flowing rivers</para>
        <para id="id1171809918499">with green, green bushes on their banks</para>
        <para id="id1171793508192">and fish, many fish swimming in the water of the river.</para>
        <para id="id1171795886418">And there were animals.</para>
        <para id="id1171810181383">animals of every kind</para>
        <para id="id1171798158870">big ones, huge ones, tall ones and small ones</para>
        <para id="id1171809949229">and they all lived in peace with one another.</para>
        <para id="id1171807154565">There was enough space for all the animals.</para>
        <para id="id1171809426298">There was enough food for all the animals.</para>
